# Nielsen Heuristics — Kafka Tool UI

Every user-facing screen and control must satisfy [Jakob Nielsen's 10 usability heuristics](https://www.nngroup.com/articles/ten-usability-heuristics/). Use this checklist when adding or changing UI.

## 1. Visibility of system status

- Long operations (connect, test, fetch, refresh) must show **in-progress** state: disable triggering controls, show `ProgressStatusBar` or status text.
- Success and failure must be visible in the view **`ViewHeader` message area** (not modal dialogs).

## 2. Match between system and the real world

- Use plain language: "Test connection", "Connect to cluster", not cryptic labels like "Test".
- Error messages must say what failed and what to check (bootstrap servers, Kafka running, firewall).

## 3. User control and freedom

- Provide **Disconnect** to return to the connect screen.
- Destructive actions use confirmation (`UserConfirmation` with OK/Cancel).
- Users can dismiss secondary windows normally.

## 4. Consistency and standards

- Primary actions use `FormButton` / **`UI.grid().addButton()`** styling from `style.css`.
- Status and errors use `ViewHeader` + `ViewMessageModel` (not modal `Alert` for feedback).
- Follow [Eclipse UI Guidelines](https://www.eclipse.org/articles/Article-UI-Guidelines/Index.html) and `docs/UI_COMPONENTS.md`.

## 5. Error prevention

- Disable Connect/Test when no cluster is selected or while an operation is running.
- Validate broker fields before test/connect (`KafkaBrokerValidator`).

## 6. Recognition rather than recall

- Combo boxes show cluster **names**; forms use labels and placeholders (e.g. schema registry URL example).
- Pre-select the first broker when only one profile exists.

## 7. Flexibility and efficiency of use

- **Test connection** before **Connect** for quick validation without entering the app.
- Refresh and auto-refresh where lists are polled (consumer groups).

## 8. Aesthetic and minimalist design

- One primary action per row where possible; avoid duplicate controls.
- Use `EmptyStatePane` for empty lists instead of blank tables.

## 9. Help users recognize, diagnose, and recover from errors

- Errors: title + short cause + recovery hint in `ViewHeader` message banner.
- Inline validation via `FormValidationLabel` on broker forms.

## 10. Help and documentation

- Prompt text on fields documents expected format.
- `docs/UI_COMPONENTS.md` documents reusable widgets; link complex flows in `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`.

## Implementation requirements

- All UI updates run on the **JavaFX application thread** (`Platform.runLater`).
- Controllers expose `ViewMessageModel` for connect, test, and operation feedback; views bind `ViewHeader` to them.
- Use `UserConfirmation` only for destructive commitments (e.g. empty topic), not for status.
